  "body": "Version: 0.10\r\nOS: Windows 10\r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\nMany screen layouts break when Status Desktop’s window width is less than 1200px. A quick fix solution to this issue (for the MVP release) is to set the minimum window width to 1200px. \r\n\r\nThe desktop app redesign will make Status Desktop fully responsive, so this will be a non-issue in the future.\r\n\r\nOnce this change is applied, there will still be a few screens in Status desktop that don’t work correctly at a 1200px minimum width.  These bugs will be raised in separate github issues.",
